result.execSummary:
The defendant Devan A Swanson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Order for DNA given to defendant in court. Must report to the Barron County Jail today, 8/2/2022, to submit DNA sample. 
Court orders record be expunged if for one full year from today's day the defendant: goes without being arrested for any criminal offense; defendant pays off all financial obligations in full; defendant has no further contact with law enforcement that would result in criminal arrest.

In the event of non-payment of outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect all debt. Attorney Fees To Be Determined.
